review_blob: On tap at Beaver St Brewery. Fantastic west coast IPA. Smells fantastic, equivalent to an Imperial IPA like Double Jack. Beautiful off white head leaves lacing on the glass. Very hoppy taste, finishes with a taste of pine.

Had this on tap at a beerfest, now enjoying a bottle from a six pack.
Appearance - Red in color, creamy thin head.
Taste - Large amount of grapefruit upfront, with bitter hops at the end. 
Palate - Medium-to-full bodied with a bitter finish.
Overall - More enjoyable on tap, as expected, but a delicious beer in any form. Another great beer from Founders!
Well balanced IPA. Tastes a bit like a less-bold Nugget Nectar. Soft caramel flavor, lots of hops, but not much of a bitter aftertaste.
This is one of my favorite beers.  Medium bodied, with caramel sweet in perfect balance with the hops. Nice amber color and thick head. Unique, appealing taste.
